Palazzo Vecchio History | Florence Through the Ages|https://www.tickets-florence.it/palazzo-vecchio/history/|threats. The building was completed in 1314, featuring solid rusticated stonework and a distinctive 94-meter-high tower, known as Arnolfo Tower. This tower incorporated the remains of an earlier structure, the Foraboschi family's La Vacca tower,  ...    - 1299–1314: Construction began under the Republic of Florence to serve as the headquarters of the Signoria (the city’s  ...    ### Arnolfo Tower once served as a prison The formidable 95-meter-tall was sometimes used as a prison for political enemies. One of its most famous prisoners was Cosimo de’ Medici (the Elder) in 1433 before his exile. Later, in 1498, Savonarola was held and tortured here before  ...    ​ Palazzo Vecchio was constructed in 1299
