Firenze in Guerra Exhibit - The City of War|https://www.firenzeinguerra.com/en/sections/the-city-of-war/persecutory-measures-against-jews.php|1941)] From 1938 the Jewish community is subject to the “race laws”. Turned away from schools and from their positions, after the out-break of war, the Jews suffer new**persecutory measures**(internment of foreign Jews since summer of 1940 and forced recruitment for work of Italian Jews which is introduced in 1942). In Bagno a Ripoli a concentration camp is set up in**Villa la Selva**, which will be in use even after 8th September  ...    [![Young Florentine Jews recruited for work in S. Donnino (Gianfranco Sarfatti is the second from the left)  ...    * logo Regione Toscana * logo Istituto Storico della Resistenza in Toscana * logo Memorysharing © Firenze in Guerra -http://www.firenzeinguerra.com La riproduzione delle immagini nel sito è subordinata alla
